JOHANNESBURG - The mother of a 13-year-old boy is in a battle with the Home Affairs Department after it dashed his dreams of playing football overseas. Bampende Maskini, a refugee from the Democratic Republic of Congo, told Parliament on Tuesday that her son George was unable to attend a soccer tournament because of document issues at Home Affairs. Department officials turned him Maskini away at the airport. His mother is now suing the department for R451,000. Watch her full story in the video above. eNCA